Mr. Garcia stated that a proposal for repair work has been submitted and a roofing contractor assessed the roof, however no cost for repair was provided.  It is recommended that the facility contact the roofing contractor to complete the necessary repairs.

name: Short-term
b_column: Some of the accessible parking spaces did not appear to be correctly configured.  Five accessible spaces were missing an adjacent access aisle. Reconfiguration of these five accessible spaces to add an accessible aisle is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: Barren turf was observed in the grass covered slope at the north perimeter of the site. Refurbishment of the turf is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: The water heaters appeared to be in fair overall condition. However, the Kenmore-brand unit (Model 153.331543) in the Office Building appeared to be 15 years in age. Based on the effective useful life and current conditions, replacement is recommended in the coming year.

name: Short-term
b_column: Warehouse and production area roof mounted vents were observed to be in disrepair due to corrosion. It is recommended to replace corrected vents at the roof of production and warehouse buildings.

name: Short-term
b_column:
Unit Bathroom Sinks
The bathroom vanity sinks are less than 24” on center from sidewalls and do not provide a centered, 30x48” parallel approach, nor are they adaptable/roll-under for a centered, forward approach. The “covered” dwelling unit bathroom sinks should be modified to provide a usable/adaptable approach.

name: Long-term
b_column: Exterior cleaning, painting, masonry pointing, sealing

name: Short-term
b_column: Damaged pavement consisting of linear cracking, alligator cracking, and potholes was present at throughout the property. Overlay replacement and crack routing/sealing is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column:
Van-Accessible Placard Signage
It did not appear that van-accessible ADA-compliant signage was provided at the ADA parking space provided at the leasing office. Installation of compliant van-accessible signage is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: A linear crack was observed at the building's northeast exterior facade. Sidewall staining was also observed in this general location as well as adjacent to the gas meter. Additionally, one of the exterior sidewall sealant joints at the building's north facade appeared to be separating from the adjacent masonry. Repair of the sidewall crack, facade cleaning and repair of the sidewall sealant joint at these respective locations is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: Spalling and apparent freeze cracking of the curbing was noted in the western parking area.  Repairs are required.

name: Long-term
b_column: Replace EPDM and BUR roof areas with TPO system

b_column: Central water heater, Replace (101 Gordon Dr)

b_column: ADA-compliant signage indicating the location of the accessible entrance was not present at the subject property. Installation of ADA-compliant signage is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column:
Landscaping Repairs
Barren turf was observed throughout the site typical of conditions noted behind buildings along the north property perimeter. Refurbishment of the turf is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: Partner observed cracking at the concrete panels.  A structural engineer was consulted and recommended that the panels exhibiting the most significant cracks be monitored periodically with the installation of Crack Monitors across representative cracks.  A cost for installation and monitoring quarterly over the next two years is included.

name: Short-term
b_column: Partner observed issues at joints between the structural concrete panels. A structural engineer was consulted and recommended that the differential movement between the panels exhibiting the most significant movement be monitored periodically with the installation of Crack Monitors across the precast concrete panel joints.  A cost for installation and monitoring quarterly over the next two years is included.

name: Short-term
b_column: Asphalt seal coat & parking stall striping

name: Short-term
b_column: Siding and corners were observed to have impact damage at the west elevation of the showroom canopy, northeast corner of the service bay, and the upper facade and soffit of the west central building area. Water damaged ceiling tiles were also observed under both the east and west showroom canopies from apparent roof leaks. It is recommended that the damaged siding and soffit be replaced.

name: Short-term
b_column: Several concrete masonry unit blocks were observed to be damaged and have linear cracking. Repair of the noted areas is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: Ponding was observed throughout several areas of the subject property, most notable along portions of the east perimeter and northwest corner of the subject property. Installation of French or supplemental drains on the noted areas is recommended.

name: Long-term
b_column: Roof replacement - EPDM 2nd Flr and Other Misc. Areas

Asphalt Pavement Repairs

Localized repair of damaged areas, along with reapplication of seal coat and striping is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: Damaged pavement consisting of linear cracking, alligator cracking and pothole formation was noted in the asphalt adjacent the northwest elevation loading docks. Sectional full-depth replacement and crack routing/sealing is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: The upper warehouse and southeast perimeter warehouse were observed with areas of impact damage, particularly at the covered storage areas of each warehouse. Replacement of the damaged siding is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: Interior vapor leaks were noted on the roof deck at building perimeters in the freezer area. This happens when there is an active roof leak that forms ice packs on the ceiling but does not drip condensation due to the extreme indoor temperature (-20-degrees). Repair of active areas of intrusion is recommended and is assumed to be covered under the existing roof warranty, therefore, no costs have been provided.

name: Short-term
b_column: According to the site escort, considerable leaking has occurred around one of the roof vent penetrations near the southwest side of the roof. Attempts to patch the issue have been made but it is unclear if the deficiency has be resolved. Repair of the noted area is recommended at this time.

name: Short-term
b_column: Cracked concrete was noted along the trailer concrete parking pavement. Repair of the concrete is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: An inoperable roof hatch was observed during the site visit. Repair of the roof hatch is recommended at this time.

name: Short-term
b_column:
Seal Coat and Striping
Seal coat was observed to be moderately to severely worn throughout and reportedly has not been resealed in over five years, although striping has occurred more recently. Reapplication of seal coat and striping is recommended, along with as-needed crack sealing.

name: Short-term
b_column:
Unit Repairs
The bathroom ceiling fan in unit 302 was observed to be damaged, and ceiling tiles in Unit 223 living room were observed damaged and/or missing. Repair/replacement of the noted conditions is recommended.

Landscaping Repairs

b_column:
Concrete Walkway Repairs

Additional areas of cracking were observed throughout the subject property. Sectional replacement or grinding is recommended.

name: Short-term
b_column: A roofing inspection and report was performed by RRK for the Client.  The report contains recommendations for repairs and maintenance.  Immediate maintenance needs recommended include cleaning, sealant, flashing, and minor repairs.

name: Short-term
b_column:
Interior Stair Guardrails
The design of the guardrails at the stairs leading to the penthouse appears to present a safety concern due to the spacing of the vertical support members. Partner recommends installing an additional vertical support at the guardrail, as the current configuration could represent a potential fall hazard for a small person.

name: Short-term
b_column: An isolated area of step cracking was observed in the concrete masonry unit wall on the northeast corner of the subject building. In addition, another isolated area of damaged concrete masonry unit wall was observed on the southeast corner of the subject property. Repair of the noted areas is recommended.

b_column: The railing on the perimeter of the concrete ramp was observed to have corrosion at the base of some columns. Repair of the noted area is recommended.

Asphalt pavement Repairs

name: Short-term

Repainting damaged metal sections of the facades, replacing damaged metal panels due to the mechanical impacts, and repointing, resealing, and cleaning from vegetation of the brick walls is recommended.

b_column:
Patio Door Thresholds
The "covered" dwelling unit patio slider door thresholds exceed 1/2" in height and are not beveled. The thresholds should be replaced and/or modified to a maximum 1/2" height or 3/4" if beveled.

Seal Coat and Crack Sealing

b_column: Several roof areas of Buildings A, B, C, and E were observed with excessive bird defecation and activity underneath HVAC units, roof screens, and throughout surfaces. The excessive bird activity can cause early failure of the membrane, seams, sealants, and roof structures, and could be a potential health hazard. Partner recommends retaining a pest control vendor to evaluate and recommend corrective measures.

b_column:
Aluminum Wiring Evaluation
The branch wiring conductors were reported and observed to be aluminum, and have been retrofitted with CO/ALR outlets. According to the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission, CO/ALR outlets are not an appropriate long-term solution. Contracting with a licensed electrician to observe a representative sample of connections to confirm that outlets have been correctly installed and are functioning properly is recommended.
